\par\par \b \uc2  Fuel price hike must go ahead - Megawati. \b0\par\par\uc2 560 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 January 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Berni K. Moestafa, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  As protests over plans to raise fuel prices mount, President Megawati Soekarnoputri admitted that it was a tough decision but, unlike her predecessors, said the government will not back down from the plan. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said that many people may be pleasantly surprised because the fuel price hike may not go as high as the reported 30 percent increase. \par \par \uc2  "The president said the rise in fuel prices and electricity rates are unpopular moves, but they cannot be canceled either," said general chairman of the Muhammadiyah Youth organization, Imam Addaruqutni as quoted by Antara on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Imam briefed reporters after his meeting with the President, in which they discussed among other items, the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by the government's indecisiveness to set a date for the fuel price hike. \par \par \uc2  The government plans to raise the average fuel price by nearly 30 percent as part of \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  cuts in the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The move also forms part of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform target pledged to the International Monetary Fund (IMF). \par \par \uc2  The fuel price hike is set for January, but the date remains unclear. Some said Cabinet members today might decide on when exactly the fuel price hike would come into effect. \par \par \uc2  Announcing a date, however, is unwise as people will rush gas stations and kerosene retailers to stock up fuel in anticipation of the higher prices. \par \par \uc2  But critics said the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  is no less damaging. \par \par \uc2  Kerosene has been rapidly disappearing from the market since it was made known that prices could go up sometime in January. \par \par \uc2  Subsequently, in many regions prices for kerosene rose to as much as Rp 1,200 (about 11.5 U.S. cents) per liter from its official price of Rp 400. \par \par \uc2  Also, the longer the delay, the greater the likelihood that the fuel price hike protests will gain momentum. \par \par \uc2  Previous governments were very cautious about raising fuel prices, for fear of mass protests leading to political upheaval. \par \par \uc2  Former President Soeharto was forced to quit in part due to the pressure arising from the social unrest sparked by fuel price hike protests. \par \par \uc2  Then came president Abdurrahman Wahid who deferred fuel price hikes twice, a move that led to multiple inflation surges in the months preceding the planned hike. \par \par \uc2  Now, the government plans to allocate Rp 2.8 trillion in compensation funds to protect the poor from the higher fuel prices. \par \par \uc2  Imam said President Megawati told him the government wanted people to pay for their fuel and electricity, because of the huge \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  must shoulder each year. \par \par \uc2  The government aims to cut fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to Rp 30.37 trillion, or about eight percent of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  amounted to Rp 53.774 trillion last year. \par \par \uc2  Minister Dorodjatun indicated that the fuel price hike may not reach the 30 percent as previously planned. \par \par \uc2  "We are not talking about a jump, a hefty jump in the price of gasoline...What is expected by the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  is not going to be that large...It's going to amaze them," he told Reuters. \par \par \uc2  This may be possible as international fuel prices have been hovering at rates below the $22 a barrel assumed in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020110dy1a00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
