\par\par \b \uc2  Fuel price hike  \highlight22\uc2 policy \highlight\uc2  causes confusion. \b0\par\par\uc2 686 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 January 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Moch. N. Kurniawan, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government's new fuel price hike \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has created confusion among economists and legislators as fear of soaring prices of basic goods starts to haunt the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Centre for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS) economist Pande Radja Silalahi feared the fuel price increase would create new \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  as it could trigger hoarding and high inflation. \par \par \uc2  "It's worse than I thought. The previous (fuel hike) \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was simpler, clearer and better," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  Umar Juoro of the Center for Indonesian Development and \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Studies (CIDES) concurred, saying that since the domestic fuel price would be set based on the international price starting March, with the expectation of rising international oil prices ahead, people would be tempted to start hoarding fuel products and goods. \par \par \uc2  He predicted inflation to be between 12 percent and 13 percent this year, compared to the government target of 9 percent. \par \par \uc2  "It is difficult for inflation to stay as a single digit this year. Be realistic, we are now facing not only a fuel price hike, but also an increase in electricity and telephone rates," Umar said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  last year was also hit by double-digit inflation of 12.5 percent, forcing \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to keep \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  high, which created difficulties for cash-strapped businesses in obtaining badly needed bank loans and in restructuring their debts. \par \par \uc2  The government raised fuel prices by an average of 22 percent, effective Thursday, and pegged most fuel products except kerosene for households and small industry to prices in neighboring Singapore. \par \par \uc2  Among the increases, the price of gasoline was increased to Rp 1,550 per liter from Rp 1,450 and kerosene for households and small industries to Rp 600 from Rp 400. \par \par \uc2  The new prices will only apply until the end of February, and starting March they will be set based monthly on the price of the Mid Oil Platts Singapore (MOPS), although the government has also set a floor price and ceiling price to anticipate sharp fluctuation in the international price. The floor price and ceiling price for premium gasoline, for instance, is set at Rp 1,450 and Rp 1,750. \par \par \uc2  The domestic fuel prices are now set equal to or at 75 percent of the MOPS prices. \par \par \uc2  The government has said that the new fuel price hike was necessary to help ease pressure on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , heavily burdened by the massive cost of bailing out weak banks. \par \par \uc2  The new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also vital to help end rampant smuggling of subsidized fuel out of the country as set prices based on international price would no longer provide the incentive for people to smuggle fuel. \par \par \uc2  But raising fuel prices has been a politically sensitive issue in the country where millions of poor people have suffered from three years of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  hardship and where people had long been used to heavily subsidized fuel during the authoritarian rule of president Soeharto. \par \par \uc2  Legislators are also confused with the new fuel price hike \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  gave approval in November last year for a 30 percent average increase in fuel prices for 2002, not an arrangement for fuel prices to be set based on fuel prices in Singapore. \par \par \uc2  Husni Thamrin of the Golkar party said the House planned to summon Minister of Energy and Mineral Resources Purnomo Yusgiantoro next week to explain the complicated fuel prices formula. \par \par \uc2  "The (new) scheme is out of track. We never made a commitment to raise the fuel prices based on that formula," he said. \par \par \uc2  Legislator Budi Priyo Santoso sees the new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as a government trick to avoid consulting with the House in raising fuel prices in the future. \par \par \uc2  "It's a trick of the government. Three months ago (November), there was no discussion of such a plan, so my colleagues and I were surprised with the new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Pande said that pegging the price of domestic fuel products to prices in Singapore was ridiculous as the latter was not even a major oil producer. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020118dy1i0000n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
