\par\par \b \uc2  BI says inflation target still attainable. \b0\par\par\uc2 425 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 January 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) expressed optimism on Friday that inflation this year would still be within the 9 percent to 10 percent target level despite the fuel price hike \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin was also convinced that the government had carefully calculated the impact of its fuel hike \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on prices. \par \par \uc2  "It (the fuel price increase) will certainly have a temporary effect, but not in the long term. So inflation will still be okay," Sjahril told reporters on Friday. \par \par \uc2  He was speaking during an inauguration ceremony of three new deputy governors of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , namely Maulana Ibrahim, Maman Soemantri and Bun Bunan Hutapea. With the three on board, BI now has six deputy governors. The other three are Miranda Goeltom, Achjar Ilyas and Aulia Pohan. \par \par \uc2  The government raised fuel prices by an average of 22 percent Thursday, and starting March the price would be set monthly based on market prices in neighboring Singapore. \par \par \uc2  The fuel price hike was unavoidable to help ease the burden of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Some economists earlier predicted that the new fuel hike \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could trigger steep increases in the prices of goods, sending inflation to a double digit level of between 12 percent and 13 percent. \par \par \uc2  Last year, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  suffered a double-digit inflation of 12.5 percent, forcing \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to impose a high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which caused difficulties for the business sector hungry for bank loans and seeking debt restructuring deals. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has started to gradually lower its benchmark interest rate since the beginning of the month. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Minister of Trade and Industry Rini Soewandi also played down the inflationary threat fears, saying that the fuel price hike would only increase prices of goods by 4 percent to 5 percent. \par \par \uc2  Commenting on reports from consumers at marketplaces across the country, that the increase in commodity prices has gone up by more than five percent, she simply replied, "Our laws cannot impose sanctions on people who decide to raise their prices." \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom said that the current increase in prices was largely caused by the delay in the announcement of the fuel price hike. \par \par \uc2  The delay prompted some people to hoard fuel products and other goods, particularly rice. \par \par \uc2  The government was supposed to announce the fuel price hike earlier this month. \par \par \uc2  "If, in the future, we can prevent this kind of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  again, I am convinced we will be able to control inflation," she said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020121dy1j0006i\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
