\par\par \b \uc2  'Government must invest more on education and health'. \b0\par\par\uc2 537 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 January 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Reiner S., The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian government must invest more money on education and health care to help regain the high \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of the past, the United Nations say. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia spends less than any other East Asian country on education and health care as a percentage of gross national product and about one third of its children were badly malnourished, said the Indonesian Human Development Report 2001. \par \par \uc2  The report was jointly prepared by the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), the National Development Planning Agency, and the Central Bureau of Statistics. \par \par \uc2  The report released last Friday said that greater \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on human development was necessary to boost \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  productivity to create social stability. \par \par \uc2  "Rekindling Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  miracle will mean operating on two fronts simultaneously. On the one hand seeking to raise the country to higher levels of productivity. On the other hand achieving the political and social stability in which productive enterprises can develop and grow." \par \par \uc2  The report said that without a highly skilled workforce, Indonesia would face difficulties in competing in a global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  It added that the lack of government attention in boosting the quality of the workforce had caused the country to be unable to fully benefit from the surge in exports due to the weak links between large-scale exporting companies and local small and medium-sized enterprises that might have fed the former with components or intermediate goods. \par \par \uc2  It pointed out that for electronics and pharmaceuticals, imports accounted for 90 percent of export value. \par \par \uc2  Other export products with high imported components included footwear (53%), garments (49%), and textiles (34%). \par \par \uc2  "As a result, Indonesia has consistently imported more manufactured goods than it has exported," the report said. \par \par \uc2  "Stepping up to higher levels of technology will require a much greater investment in education," it said, adding that Indonesia was investing only around 1.4 percent of gross national product (GNP) on education, compared with a global average of 4.8 percent. \par \par \uc2  The report also said that boosting health care should be a top priority. \par \par \uc2  "Currently, around 30 percent of Indonesian children are moderately or severely malnourished," it said. \par \par \uc2  "Without this kind of attention, the physical and intellectual development of Indonesia's children is being compromised from the outset." \par \par \uc2  Indonesia was considered as one of the miracle economies of the Asia Pacific region in the mid-1990s with average \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of around 7 percent. But the 1997 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis had caused the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to contract by more than 13 percent in 1998, and forced the government to allocate a large part of its state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to finance bank restructuring programs and pay foreign debt. \par \par \uc2  But UNDP said that despite being deep in debt, and burdened with the heavy cost of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  restructuring at a time of political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and unfavorable external \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development, greater \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on human development was a must. \par \par \uc2  "Human development cannot be considered independently of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development - the two have to go hand in hand," the report said. \par \par \uc2  "The key, however, is to recognize how all these issues connect, the social, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the political and bring this recognition to the forefront of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  consciousness." \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020122dy1m0000n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
