 major rivers Brantas and Code - which trains pass over from West Java to East Java. \par \par \uc2  Business trains have been named after mountains, such as Argo (Mount) Lawu, Argo Bromo and Argo Gede. \par \par \uc2  KAI directors thought that Empu Jaya was probably too powerful for the train. \par \par \uc2  It was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  as to how the train got its name back in 1995. One version has it that the name Empu Jaya derives from the words "Lempuyangan", an old railway station in Yogyakarta, and "Jakarta Raya", or Greater Jakarta, the route it regularly served. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020129dy1t00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
