\par\par \b \uc2  Retail sector  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  prime mover. \b0\par\par\uc2 545 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 February 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Despite the current strained \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions, the retail sector is expected to show resilience and keep growing on the back of strong consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , thus keeping the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  wheels moving. \par \par \uc2  Economists said that the retail sector would be the prime mover of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, pushing other sectors to grow as well. \par \par \uc2  Citibank economist Anton Gunawan stated a growing retail sector came as no surprise, in line with strong consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which was the foundation of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth last year. \par \par \uc2  "The retail sector grows due to strong consumption on food-related products, textiles and durable goods, such as electronics and cars," he said over the weekend. \par \par \uc2  Standard Chartered Bank economist Fauzi Ichsan, also shared the same view: "During the crisis, it has been proven that the retail sector has managed to keep growing, even under these unfavorable conditions." \par \par \uc2  Both agreed on the importance of a growing retail sector and its contribution to overall growth, as it could generate other sectors to move. \par \par \uc2  Strong consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  allows people to spend money in retailers to fulfill their needs. \par \par \uc2  When this happens, industries related to food or clothing or electronics, will eventually grow as well, giving a boost to the whole \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity. \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Funds (IMF) stressed last week the importance of the retail sector by calling on the country's banking sector to give a larger portion of lending to retailers. \par \par \uc2  With a significant drop in exports and investment flow, the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been relying heavily on strong domestic consumption to prop up its growth. \par \par \uc2  Last year, Indonesia managed to defy a declining trend of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the region by posting an impressive 3.5 percent growth, thanks to high consumption \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The trend is expected to continue this year, with consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  surpassing exports and domestic investment, both which have been declining. \par \par \uc2  Assuming consumption remains robust, the government has targeted the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to grow by 4 percent this year. \par \par \uc2  Exports, which used to be the key mover of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, have been badly hit by the global downturn and would remain so until after the first half of the year when the world's major economies like the U.S. and Japan are expected to bounce back. \par \par \uc2  As for the domestic investment sector, analysts believe it will still be difficult to come by because of the prolonged \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Aside from the retail sector however, the construction and agriculture sector would also play an important part in moving the wheels of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  According to Anton, the construction sector grew significantly last year, especially in housing projects for medium and lower income groups, and would continue to grow this year. \par \par \uc2  "This sector is also growing, this is good, because it will generate a demand for supporting goods, such as cement, steel and so on," he said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Fauzi underscored that the agriculture sector was one of the driving forces of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as it remains the dominant sector in terms of absorbing manpower. \par \par \uc2  "Despite being a traditional sector, some 40 percent to 50 percent of workers in the country are involved in this sector," Fauzi said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020218dy2i00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
