\par\par \b \uc2  IRF fails to attract investors. \b0\par\par\uc2 469 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 March 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Adianto P. Simamora, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government's plan to establish the so-named Indonesian Recovery Fund (IRF) to help finance the revitalization of the country's industries remains \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  as foreign investors have still been reluctant to invest in the fund. \par \par \uc2  "Frankly speaking, the plan to establish the fund is not progressing as well as I had expected. Foreign investors have yet to regain their confidence (in Indonesia)," Minister of Industry and Trade Rini M. Soewandi told reporters on Monday after presiding over the start of trading at the Jakarta Stock Exchange. \par \par \uc2  Factors that discouraged investors included the stalemate in the country's privatization program, she said. \par \par \uc2  "Many of them (investors) are still waiting for the government to form a clear \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the privatization program," Rini said. \par \par \uc2  The investors are also awaiting the outcome of the sale of Bank Central Asia and are watching to see if the sale process will be carried out transparently, she said. \par \par \uc2  The bidding for BCA is now in progress, with British bank Standard Chartered Bank and American investment firm Farallon competing with each other. \par \par \uc2  The government plans to raise around Rp 6.5 trillion (about US$650 million) in privatization proceeds this year. \par \par \uc2  Last year, the government was unable to sell its stake in some state-owned companies, including cement producer PT Semen Gresik, due to strong opposition from various parties, including politicians and employees. \par \par \uc2  Last year, Rini announced plans to set up IRF to help the recovery of the country's industrial sector, which mostly remains in the doldrums due to indebtedness and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  She mentioned again the funds in the ministry's blueprint program for the revitalization of the country's industries which had yet to be approved by the Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  In the revitalization program, Rini has placed priority on four industries - textiles, electronics, footwear and pulp and paper - given their labor-intensive nature. \par \par \uc2  The growth of the industries could lead to the creation of many jobs, while their collapse could lead to the laying off of thousands of workers, she said. \par \par \uc2  In the revitalization program, Rini suggested the establishment of IRF, which comprises IRF Asset Management and IRF Venture Capital. \par \par \uc2  IRF Asset Management is aimed to quickly restructure the debts of the four sectors. \par \par \uc2  Their debts should be transferred from the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) to IRF Asset Management, which will restructure the debts on commercial terms. \par \par \uc2  "Canadian firm Manulife has expressed serious interest in supporting the program," she said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, IRF Venture Capital is aimed at providing capital for small and medium enterprises, which are active in supporting big industries. \par \par \uc2  Rini said earlier that the initial funding was expected to reach $200 million, of which the government might have to contribute $10 million. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020305dy350000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
