\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah rises to five-month high against dollar. \b0\par\par\uc2 390 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 March 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The rupiah broke through on Tuesday the Rp 10,000 level against the U.S. dollar for the first time in five months, on what dealers attributed to rising confidence in a successful sale of Bank Central Asia (BCA). \par \par \uc2  The local currency jumped to a five-month high to close at Rp 9,985 against the dollar, up from Rp 10,075 the day before, marking its strongest performance since October last year. \par \par \uc2  According to dealers, the rupiah gained support from dollar-selling by state banks believed to be acting on behalf of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency. \par \par \uc2  Since the beginning of the year, the rupiah has been steadily making short gains against its U.S. counterparts over a period that has seen few political tensions surfacing. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah's breaking the key barrier of 10,000 may come as a surprise, since the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been of little support through its interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , while Indonesia's huge foreign debt overhang continues to weigh against the local unit. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  began reducing its benchmark rates on a steady basis, which would have meant pressure on the rupiah if market sentiment had been negative. \par \par \uc2  But this was apparently not the case, and dealers attributed it to the right signals the BCA sale process was sending to the market. \par \par \uc2  Securing a successful BCA sale is expected to entice foreign investors to return, as most have been holding back their capital amid an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  investment climate here. Two foreign-led consortiums remain the final bidders for BCA. \par \par \uc2  Either of the two, if selected as the winner, would bring in much-needed dollars into the market. That should hold off corporate dollar-hunters from buying, dealers said. \par \par \uc2  Other signals that buoyed the market have been positive remarks by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and other lenders on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The IMF has assured the market that Indonesia's monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is progressing on the right track. \par \par \uc2  This year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  has assumed the rupiah to average 9,000 throughout the year. \par \par \uc2  More impressive than the rupiah, however, had been the steady rise of the local stock market, which has gained about 15 percent since the beginning of the year. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020305dy360006c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
