\par\par \b \uc2  House approves conversion of bonds in four banks. \b0\par\par\uc2 611 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 March 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  finally approved on Monday the government proposal to convert some of the fixed-rate bonds in four banks into variable-rate bonds to avoid banks suffering yet more financial trouble. \par \par \uc2  Under the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , 22.5 percent of bonds held by Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BRI) would be converted into bonds carrying variable \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  linked to the benchmark rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  SBI promissory notes. \par \par \uc2  The conversion would also be applied to 95 percent of bonds retained by Bank Tabungan Negara (BTN), 40 percent of bonds in Bank Niaga and 50 percent of bonds in Bank Bali. \par \par \uc2  BRI and BTN are state-owned banks, while Bank Niaga and Bank Bali have been nationalized by the government. \par \par \uc2  The government injected the bonds in the late 1990s to finance the recapitalization of the banks. \par \par \uc2  Currently, BRI and BTN hold Rp 29 trillion (US$2.9 billion) and Rp 13.8 trillion worth of bonds, while Bank Niaga and Bank Bali obtained Rp 9.4 trillion and Rp 5.3 worth of bonds, respectively. \par \par \uc2  But most of the bonds carry a fixed interest rate of 12 percent. \par \par \uc2  Since \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark rate has been hovering at between 16 percent and 17 percent for the past year, the banks holding fixed-rate bonds had been suffering negative spread, which if continued could lead to more financial trouble. \par \par \uc2  Other banks recapitalized by the government received bonds carrying variable rates. \par \par \uc2  Amid the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  difficulties and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , most banks have been reluctant to channel lending to the business sector and have relied on the interest of government bonds as a source of revenue. \par \par \uc2  "The House approves this conversion scheme because we can understand how important it is, as a way of consolidating our banking sector as a whole," Paskah Suzzetta said, during the final hearing session with the government. \par \par \uc2  Paskah also confirmed the move would cause an additional burden of some Rp 432 billion (US$43.2 million) to the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  covers the interest rate of the bonds. \par \par \uc2  The government has said the conversion scheme was crucial to help the banks improve their financial performance. \par \par \uc2  Improvement in the country's banking sector could well result in larger credit expansion for the real sector, which will in turn accelerate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  The House approved replacing bonds held by BTN and BRI with variable rates, on the grounds that these banks have had a good track record in channeling most of their credit to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  In the case of Bank Bali, both the government and the House agreed that steps need to be taken to put the bank in better financial shape prior to its planned merger with four other small banks. \par \par \uc2  As for Bank Niaga, a conversion was seen as necessary, not only to improve its financial condition, but also to serve as sweeteners in its divestment process for investors. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, it was also revealed in the hearing that the government had allocated around Rp 3 trillion in cash to ensure a smooth process for the planned merger of five banks including Bank Bali, Bank Universal, Bank Artha Media, Bank Prima Express, Bank Patriot. \par \par \uc2  The fund is currently deposited at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  under account number 519. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Chairman of the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) I Putu Gede Ary Suta said that the agency would seek the approval of the House this month for the planned sale of several banks this year including Bank Danamon, Bank Lippo, Bank Internasional Indonesia and the bank resulting from the above merger process. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020313dy3d0000d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
