\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Tax \highlight\uc2  holiday needed to attract investment - BKPM. \b0\par\par\uc2 551 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 April 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Adianto P. Simamora, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Indonesia must provide \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives if it hopes to compete with other countries in the region in attracting badly needed foreign investment, according to Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM) chairman Theo Toemion. \par \par \uc2  Theo said on Monday that even countries in the region with better infrastructure and security were offering \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives to attract investment. \par \par \uc2  "At this time, Indonesia no longer has the competitive advantages that can be offered to attract foreign investors ... so we must provide \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  The Japan External Trade Organization earlier suggested that the government follow the example of China and other member countries of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in providing incentives to woo foreign investors, particularly from Japan. \par \par \uc2  Japan is Indonesia's largest investor and creditor. \par \par \uc2  According to data from the ASEAN Secretariat, a number of the association's member states, including Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, Vietnam and Brunei, have offered \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays to lure foreign investors. China and South Korea also are providing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  facilities. \par \par \uc2  China, along with its territory Hong Kong, last year attracted 80 percent of the foreign direct investment (FDI) in the Asian region outside of Japan. The country offered \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays to foreign investors during the first two years of their operation. \par \par \uc2  In Indonesia, FDI approvals in 2001 dropped sharply by 41.5 percent to US$9.02 billion, compared with $15.42 billion the previous year. \par \par \uc2  Besides exports and domestic consumption, foreign investment is seen as essential in overcoming the current crisis and achieving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Foreign investors largely have shunned Indonesia since the country plunged into an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political crisis in 1998. \par \par \uc2  According to analysts, foreign investors remain reluctant to enter the country due to the continuing security problems and an unstable social and political situation. \par \par \uc2  Both local and foreign investors also repeatedly have voiced concern over \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country's legal system. \par \par \uc2  "With such a (grim) picture, we need to provide \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives," Theo asserted. \par \par \uc2  He said his office had drafted a new investment bill that would soon be submitted to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The proposed law would allow the use of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives, including \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays, to attract foreign investment. \par \par \uc2  The government abolished \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays in 1983 following the enactment of a new \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, although investors in certain sectors and areas of the country were eligible for a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  allowance facility. \par \par \uc2  But according to sources, the Ministry of Finance, which is under pressure to generate more \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue to finance the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , opposes \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives. As an alternative, the ministry has introduced several new measures such as making capital goods and raw materials exempt from import duties. \par \par \uc2  "(But) these regulations are not enough to attract investors," Theo said. \par \par \uc2  But he admitted that \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays were not the most important factor in attracting foreign investors, saying a favorable investment climate played a more significant role. \par \par \uc2  Under the investment law proposed by the Investment Coordinating Board, the government would offer such \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives and facilities as \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays, making capital goods and raw materials exempt from import duties for two years production, exempting imported capital goods from the value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and offering an exemption from dividend \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020416dy4g00002\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  'Indonesian entrepreneurs to be  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  engine'. \b0\par\par\uc2 320 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 April 2002\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Several Indonesian businessmen still have capability to create new industries and become national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  machine despite critical condition in global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , an observer said. \par \par \uc2  John Arnold, program director of Indonesia Entrepreneur of the Year contended entrepreneurship characters that have firmness and high motivation could bring the country to the level of international competition. \par \par \uc2  "Entrepreneurs constitute \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  engine of the world to create new industries and are capable of changing our point of view in seeing business in the century," he said in a press conference of Entrepreneur of the Year 2002 award organized by Ernst & Young yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to him, collective sales of 14 companies employing more than 21,000 workers increased from Rp7.3 trillion to Rp12.6 trillion in 2000 amid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in some latest years. \par \par \uc2  In addition to it, John added, total assets of the 14 companies were also up by 41% and becomes a proof to the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  "The companies were set up and chaired by Indonesian entrepreneurs who had been successfully chosen as finalists in the Ernst & Young EOY award program last year," said John Arnold. \par \par \uc2  He explained such award in Indonesia is part of global EOY program that acknowledges business success and becomes reference of world entrepreneurs worldwide. \par \par \uc2  Winners of this year's prize will compete with best entrepreneurs from other 29 countries to get the prestigious predicate as World Entrepreneur of the Year 2003. \par \par \uc2  In the occasion, Benardus Djonoputro, marketing director of Indonesia Ernst & Young believed that EOY award could spur Indonesian entrepreneurs to work harder. \par \par \uc2  "We are looking for entrepreneurs that are courage enough in taking risk and have the qualities that enable them to develop strong and long enduring business," he asserted. \par \par \uc2  Bernardus added Ernst & Young as a prominent professional service provider company is asking \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  at large to nominate their candidate for this year's winners. (tri). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020020419dy4i0005t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
