\par\par \b \uc2  ' \highlight22\uc2 Tax \highlight\uc2  holiday ineffective in attracting FDI'. \b0\par\par\uc2 599 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 April 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Adianto P. Simamora, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Plans to introduce a "\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday" would not be effective in alluring foreign investors into the country due to continuing security problems, labor disputes and legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Centre for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS) economist Pande Radja Silalahi asserted. \par \par \uc2  Pande said on Tuesday that foreign investors preferred a secure investment climate over \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives. \par \par \uc2  "According to several surveys, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays are not their top priority in entering this country, they need more certainty in doing business here," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  He added that the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition was not in good enough shape to introduce a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday. \par \par \uc2  He was responding to an earlier report that the Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM) was proposing the introduction of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday to help boost badly needed foreign direct investment (FDI) into the country. \par \par \uc2  BKPM Chairman Theo Toemion claimed that he had already won the support of President Megawati Soekarnoputri, although the plan had yet to be discussed by the Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  Theo also said that other countries in southeast Asia had provided a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday to attract foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  Calls for the introduction of a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday have also come from various quarters, including from Japanese business organizations. \par \par \uc2  But Minister of Finance Boediono, who is under pressure to generate more \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue to finance the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is likely to oppose the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday plan. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, economist Bustanul Arifin economist of the Institute for Development of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Finance (Indef) said that the government should only offer the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday facility to foreign investors with a long-term investment plan which would create a considerable number of job opportunities in the country. \par \par \uc2  He, however, warned that the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday facility could also be ineffective if the country's newly autonomous provincial governments unilaterally slapped \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  on foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  "Foreign investors are very worried about the implementation of the provincial autonomy," Bustanul said. \par \par \uc2  He also urged the government to take immediate steps to improve the investment climate here. \par \par \uc2  The government abolished \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays in 1983 following the enactment of a new \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, although investors in certain sectors and areas of the country were eligible for a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  allowance facility. \par \par \uc2  BKPM is currently drafting a new investment bill which will include the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday plan. The bill will be submitted to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  for approval in the near future. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Irmadi Lubis, a legislator from House commission V, overseeing industry and trade affairs welcomed the plan to provide \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays. \par \par \uc2  "It shows that there is a political will from the government to attract foreign investors by introducing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays," Irmadi said. \par \par \uc2  He, however, said that such a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would require a change in the existing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, First Secretary for trade at the Japanese Embassy in Jakarta Tetsu Fukuoka said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holiday \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was very important for Indonesia to attract foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  holidays are a very important step to attract foreign investors but it is not a guarantee (that investors will come)," he told The Post, pointing out that other factors such as the rule of law, labor environment and existing supporting industries were also at play. \par \par \uc2  Foreign investors have largely shunned Indonesia since the country plunged into an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political crisis in 1998. \par \par \uc2  Foreign direct investment (FDI) approvals dropped last year to US$9 billion, from $15.42 billion. In the first two months of this year, FDI fell by 79 percent to $489 million, from $2.33 billion in the same period in 2001. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020424dy4o0000k\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
