\par\par \b \uc2  Consumer confidence up in March - Survey. \b0\par\par\uc2 402 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 April 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  14 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Debbie A. Lubis, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Consumer confidence rose for a second consecutive month in March, indicating a shift in consumer sentiment from pessimism to optimism over the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, Danareksa Research Institute said in its latest monthly survey released on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  Danareksa said that the consumer confidence index edged up to 93 from 89.5. \par \par \uc2  It said that the rise was followed by an increase in both the present situation index and the expectation index. \par \par \uc2  Danareksa said that the present situation index rose by nearly 5 percent to 72.4 last month, reflecting stronger conviction that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was on the rise. \par \par \uc2  The institute said the expectation index climbed nearly four points to 108.6 last month compared to 104.7 in the previous month as consumers felt confident that the existing orderly state of affairs would continue to provide an impetus for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  The government is targeting an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 4 percent this year, to be driven mainly by consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  as export and investment are expected to slowdown amid the weak global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. \par \par \uc2  Danareksa said that perception of an upward trend in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had caused self-reinforcing and self-justifying forces which created "a liquid and busy \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  It added that sanguine consumers spend more, reactivating the circular flow of funds from consumers to producers through a chain of retailers and wholesalers. \par \par \uc2  "...the rest of consumers would follow suit to join the bandwagon in lemming-like behavior that would galvanize \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  opinion on an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery," Danareksa said. \par \par \uc2  The institute surveyed some 1,700 households across six different areas to measure the buying mood of consumers and predict their buying patterns that affected the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The survey, however, said the government should preclude \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  doubts about \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery as the consumer confidence in the government stayed virtually unchanged at 114.9, after a steady decline since August 2001. \par \par \uc2  "If people are dissatisfied with the way matters are developing, bearish sentiment will come to the fore and the upturn will turn into a downturn, especially when overriding fears of the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  future overwhelm the environment and arouse the precautionary instinct of consumers" Danareksa said. \par \par \uc2  It added that the fears would encourage consumers to take a fast exit from the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  system, causing liquidity to dry up and \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to dwindle. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020425dy4q00060\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
