ighlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would be better than last year's 3.2 percent. \par \par \uc2  "If the situation remains conducive, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth this year could fare better than last year," said BPS deputy chief La Ode Syafiuddin in a news conference. \par \par \uc2  BPS said that the GDP grew by 2.15 percent in the first quarter from the fourth quarter of last year. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth still hinges on consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the current slump in the world's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been dragging down the country's exports, while foreign direct investment would remain low as the country has yet to address various problems at home, including legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , labor unrest and a security problem. \par \par \uc2  Foreign direct investment approval was down 90 percent to US$292 million in the first quarter of this year compared to $2.44 billion in the same period last year, according to a report from the Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM). \par \par \uc2  Reports of an improvement in investor confidence in the country during the first quarter, analysts said, was mostly dominated by portfolio investment as shown in the rising stock market index and 10 percent rise in the value of the rupiah to the U.S. dollar, considered to be one of the best performing markets in the region. \par \par \uc2  Although the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could grow by 4 percent this year, the government is still facing an uphill task as the growth figure is not sufficient to absorb the millions of unemployed people. \par \par \uc2  Experts have said that the country needs to have growth of between 6 percent and 7 percent to be able to absorb the huge unemployment. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020516d