\par\par \b \uc2  Speedy help needed for SMEs - KPEN. \b0\par\par\uc2 621 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 June 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  14 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Fitri Wulandari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee (KPEN) urged the government to speed up the restructuring of debts owed by small and medium enterprises (SMEs), and to apply tariffs on four commodities to protect domestic industry. \par \par \uc2  KPEN chairman Sofyan Wanandi said on Thursday that the government should pay greater attention to SMEs given their important role in speeding up the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery amid the current global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump. \par \par \uc2  He said foreign direct investment in the country was expected to slow down in the future as investor confidence declined due to the collapse of many big corporations worldwide and the legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  faced by foreign investors now operating in the country. \par \par \uc2  "We predict that FDI in Indonesia will be scarce in the future. Therefore, we have very limited options for saving our industry and \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Sofjan told a press conference. \par \par \uc2  The KPEN urged the government to speed up the issuance of the planned presidential decree on SME debt restructuring as many such debts were non-performing. \par \par \uc2  SME debt restructuring was important for the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as SMEs had proven their ability to weather the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis and to employ huge numbers of people. \par \par \uc2  "The government must pay serious attention to the SMEs because it is these that are really going to save us, particularly as regards employment," he said. \par \par \uc2  Sofjan referred to a recent statement made by Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Dorodjatun Kuntjoro Jakti saying that the government would issue a decree on the restructuring of SME bad debts in early July. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun said total SME bad debts amounted to Rp 28.1 trillion (about US$3.2 billion). \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has also signed an agreement with the country's banks for the distribution of a total of Rp 30 trillion in loans to SMEs. \par \par \uc2  Aburizal Bakrie, chairman of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce (Kadin) said that the decree would give the banks a legal basis for restructuring their SME loans. \par \par \uc2  "The SMEs should be able to run their businesses better and to access loans," said Aburizal, who also attended the press conference. \par \par \uc2  In addition, the KPEN also urged the government to set clear cut policies in applying measures to protect four domestic commodity producers - those of rice, sugar, soybeans and corn. \par \par \uc2  "We can use quotas, tariffs or whatever else to protect our farmers. The government should apply these measures, not just talk about it," Sofjan said. \par \par \uc2  Over the past few years, imported rice, corn, soybeans and sugar have been flooding the domestic market and threatening local producers given their lower prices. \par \par \uc2  At present, Indonesia imposes a 30 percent import \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  on rice, and tariffs of between 20 percent and 25 percent on sugar. There are currently no tariffs on corn and soybeans. \par \par \uc2  Recently, the government has said it would apply higher tariffs on the four commodities. A team set up to formulate the tariffs is expected to complete its work next month. \par \par \uc2  The KPEN did not suggest any \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  figures. \par \par \uc2  However, Sofjan suggested that while such tariffs should benefit farmers, they should not burden consumers. \par \par \uc2  The KPEN further called on the government to enact \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  that would support the bringing about of a better investment climate. \par \par \uc2  "The government should produce policies and laws which can provide stability not only for domestic businesses but also foreign investors," Aburizal said. \par \par \uc2  He cited the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on wages, which had caused concern for businessmen and foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  However, he said that the coming law on labor affairs, which was currently being debated in the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  could provide fair solutions to the problems. \par \par \uc2  "The law should protect both workers and industry," he remarked. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020628dy6s0000l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
