\par\par \b \uc2  New labor bill could turn foreign investors away. \b0\par\par\uc2 561 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 July 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Businessmen criticized the new bill on labor protection and development as "overly protective" and at the expense of investors, saying that if it is passed into law, it will further deteriorate the country's business climate. \par \par \uc2  "If the bill is passed into law, many investors will leave the country and look for other places to invest in," chairman of the National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee (KPEN) Sofjan Wanandi told The Jakarta Post last week. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Manpower and Transmigration Jacob Nua Wea is lobbying the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  to complete the debate on the bill quickly so President Megawati Soekarnoputri can sign it in October. \par \par \uc2  The House is scheduled to separately meet with businessmen and workers this week to discuss the matter. \par \par \uc2  "The bill is overly protective (on workers)," Sofjan said. \par \par \uc2  According to the bill, companies must continue paying workers their wages, even if they were on strike. \par \par \uc2  Under the draft, when a worker stages a strike or is facing criminal charges in court, it means the worker is failing to fulfill their daily duties, yet the company will still have to pay the worker's salary during a strike or for the duration of a trial until the court's verdict. \par \par \uc2  Also uncommon by any standards is a clause stating a company has to pay severance payments to workers who voluntarily resign. \par \par \uc2  Night-shift workers will not be allowed to work more than 35 hours per week, which is five hours shorter than the current \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which in turn will lower productivity, eventually making companies less competitive. \par \par \uc2  Sofjan said that with such a ruling, Indonesian manufacturing industries would become even less productive than their peers in the region, which have been calling for more than 40-hours per week work for their workers. \par \par \uc2  Another clause that could scare off investors is that the violation of all labor regulations could risk a jail term. \par \par \uc2  "This is unbelievable. No such regulations exist in other countries. With this \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  who would come here and invest their money, they would be better off looking to invest in neighboring countries, such as China or Vietnam," Sofjan said. \par \par \uc2  Anton Supit, chairman of the Indonesian Footwear Association, agreed. \par \par \uc2  "(Minister) Jacob thinks our country is already wealthy so it has proposed a sophisticated labor bill," he said. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have said that in addition to security issues, legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and disputes over the new autonomy law, labor issues were a significant factor in scaring away investors. \par \par \uc2  All these factors have resulted in approvals for foreign direct investment (FDI) and domestic investment during the first five months of this year dropping by between 59 percent and 30 percent, respectively, compared to the same period in 2001. \par \par \uc2  The Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM) disclosed last week that as of May 30, FDI approvals stood at US$1.67 billion, far below the $3.98 billion posted during the same period last year. As for domestic investment, it dropped to Rp 9.4 trillion from Rp 12.7 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Sunarty of the Indonesian Prosperity Trade Union (SBSI), brushed aside the concerns saying the new bill was a result of discussions with various parties, including businessmen. \par \par \uc2  However, she urged both businessmen and workers to sit together and hold talks more often to produce better understanding. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020701dy710000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
