\par\par \b \uc2  Megawati revives 13 'mega' projects worth $7.63 billion. \b0\par\par\uc2 585 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 July 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Fabiola Desy Unidjaja and Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Cikampek, West Java \par \par \uc2  In a bid to show signs of reviving investor confidence in the country, President Megawati Soekarnoputri officially recommenced on Wednesday 13 mega projects worth US$7.63 billion with the hope that these would serve as the engines of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the coming years. \par \par \uc2  Megawati said she expected these projects would become a catalyst to lure more investments to help ignite the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Next month, 80 other projects will be renegotiated to recommence. All this should be able to get our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on track," Megawati said during a ground-breaking ceremony for the expansion of PT Pupuk Kujang fertilizer plant in Cikampek, West Java. \par \par \uc2  She also symbolically inaugurated 12 other projects in seven provinces, including in Aceh, East Kalimantan, South Sulawesi, North Sulawesi and West Java. \par \par \uc2  Also present were Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti, Coordinating Minister for People's Welfare Yusuf Kalla, and Minister of Mines and Energy Purnomo Yusgiantoro. \par \par \uc2  The projects were halted in 1997 by the previous government of Soeharto in the wake of the regional financial crisis. \par \par \uc2  The relaunch of such projects should provide a glimmer of hope that amid the many discouraging signs in the country, investors would still come and invest. \par \par \uc2  With the funding for the projects coming mostly from foreign investors, especially the Japan Bank for International Corporations (JBIC), the government expects this would restore investor confidence in the country. \par \par \uc2  "The successful negotiations for these projects should augur well for future ones" Dorodjatun said. \par \par \uc2  This has come amid lingering fears that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery would be dealt a huge blow following recent data showing signs of setbacks in various macroeconomics indicators. \par \par \uc2  In the first five months of the year, not only did the foreign direct investment (FDI) approvals decline, the country also experienced a sharp drop in exports. \par \par \uc2  Both could have been the country's prime mover for its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  FDI approval between January to May plunged by almost 60 percent to $1.7 billion from $3.98 billion posted during the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  Exports in the first five months of the year also recorded an almost 10 percent drop compared to the same period in 2001. \par \par \uc2  Although this must have something to do with the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown, internal factors are also believed to have played a significant part in deteriorating confidence on the part of investors in the country. \par \par \uc2  Among other things, legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , confusion about regional autonomy and labor-related disputes served as the main obstacles for robust capital inflows. \par \par \uc2  As the government's efforts to improve those conditions seem to be hitting snags, concerns are high that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook remains bleak. \par \par \uc2  The only good news the government can boast of is that its currency has been showing a strong performance against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  Such a development should be hailed as encouraging, as this would lead to a more manageable inflation, thus providing more leeway for a lower interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's promissory notes. \par \par \uc2  However, analysts attributed the strengthening of the rupiah more to the bearish trend of the dollar in the region, therefore this has only little to do with internal conditions. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Dorodjatun said that the projects, which are categorized into petrochemical, electricity and fertilizer projects, would help move the wheel of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities as it would also absorb thousands of workers. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020704dy740000o\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
