t \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets for the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  are: an exchange rate of between Rp8,500 and Rp9,500 to the US dollar, an inflation rate of between 7 percent and 9 percent, \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's three-month SBI promissory notes of between 12.5 percent and 14.5 percent, and oil prices of US$19 to US$22 per barrel. Ross said the inflation target of 7 percent to 9 percent could be achieved if monetary policies in 2002 and 2003 showed signs of improvement. This was the result of the government's success to curb the money supply, he said. "I am optimistic that the inflation rate could be controlled as long as \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  maintains the tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  with regard to money supply," he said. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020020716dy7d0007a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
