\par\par \b \uc2  Lower  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\uc2  key for  \highlight22\uc2 deficit \highlight\uc2  control. \b0\par\par\uc2 666 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 July 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Fitri Wulandari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Although the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the first semester of this year turned out to be much lower than predicted, economists said the government still had to work extra hard to maintain a "favorable domestic environment" to help ensure that the full-year \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not inflate beyond the safe limit. \par \par \uc2  Raden Pardede said that the favorable environment would give room for \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to continue to guide \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  lower, which in turn would ease the burden of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in covering the interest cost of government bonds. \par \par \uc2  "A one percent increase in \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  means the government must pay an additional Rp 2.3 trillion (US$258 million) in domestic debt. Lowering interest would certainly ease the government's burden," Raden told The Jakarta Post over the weekend. \par \par \uc2  The government issued over Rp 430 trillion worth of bonds to recapitalize ailing banks in the late 1990s. The bond \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  is attached to the interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  SBI promissory notes. \par \par \uc2  For this year alone, the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  must allocate some Rp 60 trillion for interest payments - the largest \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  item. \par \par \uc2  If the government manages to control this \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not explode beyond the Rp 42 trillion or 2.5 percent of gross domestic product limit. \par \par \uc2  The Ministry of Finance recently reported that for the first semester of 2002, the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  was Rp 7.1 trillion or 16.8 percent of this year's limit of Rp 42 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The number was much lower than earlier predicted by the government and the International Monetary Fund at Rp 14 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Analysts, however, explained that with a fraction of the recap bonds to mature in the second half, combined with signs of the rupiah weakening once again, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  could be prompted to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the second semester which would endanger the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  target. \par \par \uc2  Umar Juoro said the government must somehow lower domestic debt burdens because that was the only way to compensate for the slumping exports and foreign direct investment. \par \par \uc2  "There is no significant chance to increase revenue from other sectors. This (lowering domestic debt) is the only way," he told The Post. \par \par \uc2  The interest rate for one-month SBI notes have been on a declining trend since the beginning of the year amid a stronger rupiah and slowing inflation. The rate is currently less than 15 percent compared to more than 18 percent late last year. \par \par \uc2  But the rupiah has been under heavy pressure lately, breaking the Rp 9,000 level for the first time in two months last week. Analysts said that in addition to global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and the upcoming August Annual Session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) investors were getting increasingly jittery. A weak rupiah could reignite inflation. \par \par \uc2  In terms of first half revenue, the government managed to get Rp 130.5 trillion, compared to the full-year target of Rp 301 trillion. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the first semester reached Rp 137.6 trillion, compared to the 2002 target of Rp 344 trillion. \par \par \uc2  For revenue, however, the two economists have different opinions on whether the government should continue to rely on \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the main source of income. \par \par \uc2  Raden agreed that the government must focus on \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  to increase revenue. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  still makes up 70 percent of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue with this year's target of Rp 219.6 trillion. According to the Ministry of Finance, as of June, the government managed to raise Rp 130 trillion in \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Umar voiced a different opinion saying that relying on \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  would only burden the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  which at present was driven mainly by domestic consumption. \par \par \uc2  "Pushing \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the main source of revenue would only put pressure on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities and domestic consumption," Umar said. \par \par \uc2  Umar said what the government should do was to improve the domestic climate to lure more investors back in. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020715dy7f0000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
