\par\par \b \uc2  Business sentiment strengthens but legal  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties \highlight\uc2  remain. \b0\par\par\uc2 433 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 July 2002\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Fitri Wulandari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The country's Business Sentiment Index (BSI) rose for the second consecutive period, as more business leaders expressed confidence about their current performance and their business outlook for the next six months, a survey said. \par \par \uc2  According to the Danareksa Research Institute survey of top executives at leading companies for the April-May period, the BSI climbed to 111.3 from 110.2. \par \par \uc2  "The higher investor sentiment stressed greater confidence in the vigor of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, which signifies a prelude to stronger growth ahead for both the nation's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and companies' financial conditions," the survey said. \par \par \uc2  According to the survey, the Present Situation Index (PSI) climbed to 100.9 from 100.3, and the Expectations Index (EI) rose from 120.2 to 121.6, which contributed to the rising BSI. \par \par \uc2  The Danareksa survey covered 700 chief executives or directors from a wide variety of leading companies in various sectors, ranging from construction, agriculture and mining, to hotels and restaurants. \par \par \uc2  The survey was designed to measure CEOs' assessments of current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and business conditions, as well as their expectations for the next six months. \par \par \uc2  While the BSI rose, the Business Confidence in the Government Index (BCGI) plunged for the fourth straight time to 104.6 from 106.1. The BCGI's decline was due to a plunge in sentiment about law enforcement, which hit a fresh low of 78.7. \par \par \uc2  "The index reflects doubt about committing fresh funds to expand capacity," Danareksa remarked. \par \par \uc2  This doubt, Danareksa said, has emerged amid expected improvements in corporate profitability and liquidity over the next six months, brought about by an anticipated slide in the benchmark interest rate on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's SBI promissory notes and the appreciation of the rupiah against the US dollar. \par \par \uc2  With stocks of finished goods almost exhausted, more CEOs believe existing capacity needs to be expanded to sustain profit growth, as the increasing use of production capacity approaches its limits. \par \par \uc2  "CEOs, however, have to think about the safety of committing large sums of money in advance of financial returns against any risks to the future life of their business operations," Danareksa pointed out. \par \par \uc2  Business leaders are waiting for signs that the government is committed to protecting entrepreneurs. \par \par \uc2  "The most prominent threat is the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of whether the state can enforce a valid contract if any party to the contract reneges unfairly," it added. \par \par \uc2  Without legal assurance, the translation of sanguine sentiment into stronger fundamentals remains at best a fashionable topic for talk shows, Danareksa stressed. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2002 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020020715dy7g000he\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Political parties commitment to help reducing inflation. \b0\par\par\uc2 672 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 July 2002\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2002 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Although the meeting of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  board of governors has cautioned of the mounting pressures on inflation ahead of MPR (People's Consultative Assemny) yearly session, the pressure was expected to be reduced by big political parties commitment to ensure security. \par \par \uc2  Anwar Nasution, senior deputy governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said MPR yearly session (ST-MPR) need not spark any fear as the political situation was relatively secure. Besides political factor, he continued, the fundamental of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was accordingly improving. \par \par \uc2  "Pak Amin Rais (MPR speaker as well as PAN - the National Mandate Party - head) has said there would not be any turbulences. All big political parties also had echoed similar commitment. So, I think there would not be anything to worried about," he told reporters at DPR (\b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Anwar said if any inflation pressure would occure, it would go to imported foods. Inflation could be triggered by rupiah's fall. \par \par \uc2  However he said the price of imported goods could be covered by the upcoming harvest products. "Bungaran had said so. There should not be anything to be worried about. There would not be any stoppage accordingly." \par \par \uc2  In the meeting of BI board of governors, they warned of risk and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors ahead of ST-MPR that had potency of enhancing negative sentiments. \par \par \uc2  Governor of BI Syahril Sabirin earlier said although pressures on inflation were still hovering about, BI was still optimistic that inflation target of 2002 could be met. \par \par \uc2  Besides, BI predicted pressure on inflation to be mounting in upcoming months due to disturbance of dry season-generated food supply. "However the inflation target of 9% to 10% could be met," he said. \par \par \uc2  The meeting also concluded that pressures on inflation rate during the second quarter of 2002 were still occuring due to government-tuned price policies. \par \par \uc2  On the other hand the rupiah was predicted to go on strengthening. But BI cautioned of risk and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors ahead of ST-MPR that could enhance negative sentiments. \par \par \uc2  Rupiah depreciation \par \par \uc2  Anwar acknowledged in the last two weeks rupiah has been undervalued. \par \par \uc2  Rupiah was traded at around Rp9,030 to Rp9,100 against US$ yesterday - thus relatively stable compared to that of previous day, but was drastically lower compared to that of two weeks earlier at 115.45 to 116.45 against yen and 1.0026 to 1.0148 against euro. \par \par \uc2  However, Anwar said the rupiah weakening was temporary. \par \par \uc2  Citing as an example, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamental has been improving thanks to IBRA efforts, including asset to bond swap plan that was to be implemented soon. \par \par \uc2  "So after being restructured, the non-performing loans (NPLs) or our banks would be more helped." \par \par \uc2  The pressure on the rupiah rate, he continued, would be supported by the private debt restructuring which had been a committement of the Jakarta Initiatives. \par \par \uc2  Even Anwar said the pressures on the rupiah from private sector was still remaining within a proper limit. "If there were corporate sector that inflicted pressures, it did need US$ to meet its international liabilities. It could probably to pay debt." \par \par \uc2  He even believed in the future prospect of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as government had sparked a positive signal into the market. For example, to put it simply, the commitment to implement Bank Niaga divestment, to sell Bank Mandiri, as well as merger of five banks. \par \par \uc2  "We hope that there would not be fireworks frenzy, and ST-MPR would not be disturbed." \par \par \uc2  The minister of finance Boediono also said the prospect of Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  during the second quarter of 2002 would be better on the ground that a lot of factors contributing at the conducive environtment for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could be maintained. He predicted the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would grow at 4% throughout this year. \par \par \uc2  Besides, Boediono said the controllable amount of circulating money as well as the strengthening of many currencies - thus the falling rupiah would recover - would help reducing the pressures on inflation. \par \par \uc2  "For the whole year the inflation rate would be not over than 9.5%," he said. (aph). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020020718dy7h00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
